web:type.web:oldSection:
Thought and Reflection


Watch Night Service
New Years Eve 2010

It was a blessed event. Over 50 strong in attendance. We brought in the New Year with communion, song, prayer and praise. Being in the house of the LORD is always good and on this night the message of the evening was "STAY FOCUSED" because "THE BEST IS YET TO COME". We gave thanks for all HE has done and all HE has in store for 2011, you only need to be saved and believe in your heart. At St. Paul's Baptist Church, change is  the order of the day.
web:type.web:newSection:
Thought and Reflection


Church Meeting 12/5/2011

A congregational meeting was held on Monday, December 5 2011. The primary focus of the meeting was to provide a financial summary of the past year and a budget proposal for the upcoming year 2012. This was a very informative meeting in that it has been quite some time since a finance meeting was conducted. That being said, it was without some bumps as the discussion moved off topic a bit and centered on committees and organizational hierarchy. Of the positives discussed was the process of submitting a proposal and vouchers for 2012 events and programs supported by St. Pauls Baptist Church. Budget proposals for the year 2012 are to be submitted by the end of February 2012 for review and approval by church leadership. Forms have been added to the website for ministries to submit. The meeting closed with a prayer.
